    {
      "content": "Conditions that must be met to delete an Azure AD directory",
      "pos": [
        12288,
        12347
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure AD requires that certain conditions are met to delete a directory.",
      "pos": [
        12349,
        12421
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This reduces risk that deletion of a directory would negatively impact users or applications, such as the ability of users to sign in to Office 365 or access resources in Azure.",
      "pos": [
        12422,
        12599
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, if a directory for a subscription became unintentionally deleted, then users could not access the Azure resources for that subscription.",
      "pos": [
        12600,
        12749
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following conditions are checked:",
      "pos": [
        12751,
        12788
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The only user in the directory is the global administrator who will delete the directory.",
      "pos": [
        12792,
        12881
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Any other users must be deleted before the directory can be deleted.",
      "pos": [
        12882,
        12950
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If users are synchronized from on-premises, then sync will need to be turned off, and the users must be deleted in the cloud directory by using the Management Portal or the Azure module for Windows PowerShell.",
      "pos": [
        12951,
        13160
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There is no requirement to delete groups or contacts, such as contacts added from the Office 365 Admin Center.",
      "pos": [
        13161,
        13271
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There can be no applications in the directory.",
      "pos": [
        13274,
        13320
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Any applications must be deleted before the directory can be deleted.",
      "pos": [
        13321,
        13390
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There can be no subscriptions for any Microsoft Online Services such as Microsoft Azure, Office 365, or Azure AD Premium associated with the directory.",
      "pos": [
        13393,
        13544
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, if a default directory was created for you in Azure, you cannot delete this directory if your Azure subscription still relies on this directory for authentication.",
      "pos": [
        13545,
        13721
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Similarly, you cannot delete a directory if another user has associated a subscription with it.",
      "pos": [
        13722,
        13817
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To associate your subscription with a different directory, sign in to the Azure Management Portal and click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> in the left navigation.",
      "pos": [
        13818,
        13962
      ]
    },
    {
